      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is creatine safe for men over 40?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — creatine monohydrate has one of the strongest safety profiles of any supplement. Decades of research show no adverse effects on kidney function in healthy adults at 3–5g daily. Men with existing kidney disease should consult a physician first. The main side effect is mild water retention in muscle tissue during the first few weeks.</div>
